<item>
            <title>[CODEC-145] Base64.encodeBase64String could better use newStringUsAscii</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-145</link>
                <project id="12310464" key="CODEC">Commons Codec</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Base64.encodeBase64String&lt;/tt&gt; currently uses &lt;tt&gt;StringUtils.newStringUtf8&lt;/tt&gt;. But the text should be in fact be in ASCII, so &lt;tt&gt;newStringUsAscii&lt;/tt&gt; would be clearer and perhaps faster.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
